    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-25T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-25T23:00:00-05:00" n="683"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d683">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/11099</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SJH1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Shea</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-26T00:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 26, 1918, 12 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.21 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Embassy’s telegram of August 9, 2 p.m. Much activity in official quarters. <hi
                        rend="italic">La Nacion</hi>, controlled by Señor
                    <persName>Yanez</persName>, in leading editorial yesterday urges action be taken
                    to acquire German ships. <hi rend="italic">Mercurio</hi> of this morning has
                    editorial on the same lines. Am of opinion that a direct intimation that it will
                    be necessary very soon to divert the <hi rend="italic">Santa Ana</hi> and one or
                    two British vessels from west coast trade would have good effect and might bring
                    quick settlement. For good of local conditions intimation should be made
                    quickly. It will also help the situation if it is intimated that hereafter our
                    ships will be devoted to nitrate trade exclusively and will therefore not come
                    south of Antofagasta.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SJH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shea</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
